  79      """Read-only sequence object (essentially a string with an alphabet). 
  80   
  81      Like normal python strings, our basic sequence object is immutable. 
  82      This prevents you from doing my_seq[5] = "A" for example, but does allow 
  83      Seq objects to be used as dictionary keys. 
  84   
  85      The Seq object provides a number of string like methods (such as count, 
  86      find, split and strip), which are alphabet aware where appropriate. 
  87   
  88      In addition to the string like sequence, the Seq object has an alphabet 
  89      property. This is an instance of an Alphabet class from Bio.Alphabet, 
  90      for example generic DNA, or IUPAC DNA. This describes the type of molecule 
  91      (e.g. RNA, DNA, protein) and may also indicate the expected symbols 
  92      (letters). 
  93   
  94      The Seq object also provides some biological methods, such as complement, 
  95      reverse_complement, transcribe, back_transcribe and translate (which are 
  96      not applicable to sequences with a protein alphabet).
